                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 8.487,
                                "byte_start": 87589,
                                "byte_stop": 121548,
                                "text": "The opinion of the court in number 00-6029 Ragsdale versus Wolverine World Wide will be announced by Justice Kennedy."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 8.487,
                        "stop": 209.633,
                        "byte_start": 121548,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15113,
                            "name": "Anthony M. Kennedy",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/anthony_m_kennedy",
                            "last_name": "Kennedy",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2757,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 572162400,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Ronald Reagan",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2757"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32679,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 47100,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/anthony_kennedy_1_3.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 10147,
                            "identifier": "anthony_m_kennedy"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 8.487,
                                "stop": 43.909,
                                "byte_start": 121548,
                                "byte_stop": 263236,
                                "text": "This case involves an employee and employer who were covered by the Family and Medical Leave Act -- that is Federal statute is which sometimes referred to as FMLA -- under the act, the employees are guaranteed 12 weeks of unpaid leave each year for certain specified purposes and the employer here, Wolverine World Wide Inc. granted its employee and her name is Tracy Ragsdale 30-weeks of leave when her cancer condition kept her out of work in 1996."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 43.909,
                                "stop": 49.757,
                                "byte_start": 263236,
                                "byte_stop": 286642,
                                "text": "So, the act requires 12 weeks the employer granted 30 weeks."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 49.757,
                                "stop": 62.965,
                                "byte_start": 286642,
                                "byte_stop": 339514,
                                "text": "The employer however did not designate in advance that the leave she took would count as FMLA leave as a regulation of the Department of Labor requires the employer to do."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 62.965,
                                "stop": 69.468,
                                "byte_start": 339514,
                                "byte_stop": 365532,
                                "text": "Ragsdale sued the employer containing that because no advance notice was given to her, she was entitled to 12 more weeks of leave."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 69.468,
                                "stop": 75.57,
                                "byte_start": 365532,
                                "byte_stop": 389878,
                                "text": "Under her theory this additional leave and not the leave she had taken would be the FMLA leave."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 75.57,
                                "stop": 79.684,
                                "byte_start": 389878,
                                "byte_stop": 406387,
                                "text": "A specific regulation issued by the Secretary of Labor supported her position."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 79.684,
                                "stop": 93.503,
                                "byte_start": 406387,
                                "byte_stop": 461662,
                                "text": "The employer asserted that the regulation requiring the additional leave in every case where notice is not given but without any injury to the employee was invalid because it was beyond the secretary\u2019s authority under the act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 93.503,
                                "stop": 97.49,
                                "byte_start": 461662,
                                "byte_stop": 477649,
                                "text": "The District Court agreed that the regulation was invalid and granted summary judgment to the employer."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 97.49,
                                "stop": 102.041,
                                "byte_start": 477649,
                                "byte_stop": 495831,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals also agreed with the employer disposition and we now affirm."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 102.041,
                                "stop": 106.039,
                                "byte_start": 495831,
                                "byte_stop": 511818,
                                "text": "The Secretary\u2019s regulation is inconsistent with the structure of the Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 106.039,
                                "stop": 116.235,
                                "byte_start": 511818,
                                "byte_stop": 552569,
                                "text": "The Act allows employees to sue employers but it requires that the employees show that their rights under the statute were violated and that they suffered some specific injury."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 116.235,
                                "stop": 120.947,
                                "byte_start": 552569,
                                "byte_stop": 571481,
                                "text": "In the case at hand, the employee\u2019s rights were not violated and she suffered no injury."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 120.947,
                                "stop": 126.829,
                                "byte_start": 571481,
                                "byte_stop": 594991,
                                "text": "She would have taken the entire 30-week absence even if the employer had complied with the notice requirement."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 126.829,
                                "stop": 136.997,
                                "byte_start": 594991,
                                "byte_stop": 635638,
                                "text": "The regulation nevertheless transformed the company\u2019s failure to give notice along with its refusal to grant her more than 30-weeks of leave into an actionable violation of the statute."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 136.997,
                                "stop": 148.289,
                                "byte_start": 635638,
                                "byte_stop": 680778,
                                "text": "Furthermore the Secretary\u2019s penalty amends that FMLA\u0027s most fundamental substantive guarantee the employee\u2019s entitlement to a total of 12-work weeks of leave during any 12 month period."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 148.289,
                                "stop": 153.799,
                                "byte_start": 680778,
                                "byte_stop": 702825,
                                "text": "The 12 week figure was the result of compromise between groups with marked but divergent interests."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 153.799,
                                "stop": 163.358,
                                "byte_start": 702825,
                                "byte_stop": 741068,
                                "text": "The Secretary\u2019s chosen penalty subverts the careful balance, for it gives certain employee a right to more than 12 weeks of FMLA compliant leave."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 163.358,
                                "stop": 180.671,
                                "byte_start": 741068,
                                "byte_stop": 810345,
                                "text": "In defense of the regulation, the Government notes that a categorical penalty requiring the employer to grant more leave is easier to administer than one involving a fact specific inquiry into what steps the employee would have taken had the employer given the required notice."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 180.671,
                                "stop": 192.138,
                                "byte_start": 810345,
                                "byte_stop": 856216,
                                "text": "Regardless of how serious the problem an administrative agency seeks to address, however, it may not exercise its authority in a manner inconsistent with the administrative structure Congress enacted into law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 192.138,
                                "stop": 200.776,
                                "byte_start": 856216,
                                "byte_stop": 890698,
                                "text": "These and other considerations explained in the opinion persuade us that the regulation cannot be within the Secretary\u2019s priority issue rules necessary to carry out the act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 200.776,
                                "stop": 202.944,
                                "byte_start": 890698,
                                "byte_stop": 899370,
                                "text": "The judgment of the Court of Appeals was affirmed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 202.944,
                                "stop": 209.633,
                                "byte_start": 899370,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice O\u2019Connor has written a dissenting opinion in which Justices Souter, Ginsburg and Breyer have joined."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
